## English Summary

### Core Events

- [18:45] United Arab Emirates announces alternative shipping lanes to应对 Hormuz Strait blockade
- [18:30] International Energy Agency holds emergency meeting to discuss global oil supply crisis response
- [18:15] India announces strategic petroleum reserve activation to应对 oil price surge economic pressure
- [18:00] US Seventh Fleet continues military exercises in Arabian Sea, maintaining high alert status

### Military Developments

- USS Lincoln Carrier Strike Group conducts air defense exercises in Arabian Sea during nighttime
- Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps Navy conducts anti-ship missile test launches near Strait of Hormuz
- Israeli Air Force increases patrol frequency in southern Lebanon border, intelligence suggests preparation for new actions
- Persian Gulf shipping insurance rates rise 40%, some shipping companies choose Cape of Good Hope route

### Economic Impact

- Global oil prices突破 $95/barrel, reaching highest level in nearly three years
- Asian fuel prices大幅上涨,部分地区出现 panic buying现象
- US gasoline prices hit all-time high, Trump administration faces domestic pressure
- EU announces energy emergency mechanism activation, coordinating member states应对 supply crisis

### Diplomatic Developments

- UN Secretary-General再次呼吁人道主义走廊, but implementation details still under negotiation
- China and Russia submit new resolution draft at Security Council, calling for restraint from both parties
- Arab foreign ministers meeting in Cairo to discuss regional stability方案
- Turkey continues shuttle diplomacy between Doha and Riyadh

### Humanitarian Situation

- UN World Food Programme reports worsening food supply shortages in southern Iran
- International Red Cross medical convoy experiences delays at Syria-Iran border
- Iranian Ministry of Health reports 70% medical supplies shortage rate nationwide,急需 international aid
- UNHCR updates data: 780,000 displaced persons now in Iran

