### Analysis

Iran War enters hour 73 with economic impacts beginning to manifest, global oil markets experiencing panic-driven price increases. Military standoff continues, but both sides face significant international pressure and economic costs. International mediation efforts, though advancing slowly, lack breakthrough progress. Humanitarian crisis is intensifying, requiring more active international action to alleviate civilian suffering. The coming weeks will be a critical testing period, with developments depending on balancing multiple factors.

